Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.95,0:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You... cowards!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.00,0:00:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Just shut up...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.66,0:00:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,...and invest everything in me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.00,0:00:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What you need now
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.25,0:00:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be taught a lesson,\Nnot given a talking-to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.70,0:00:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've reached my decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.54,0:00:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren was placed in the\NScout Regiment's custody
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.41,0:00:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in preparation for a scouting\Nmission beyond the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.04,0:01:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I won't let your deaths be meaningless{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.75,0:01:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}even if I'm the last one standing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.87,0:01:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In both hands, Gloria{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.75,0:01:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What sings is Sieg{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.75,0:01:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}On my back, Flügel der Freiheit{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.87,0:01:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Clenched determination to my left chest{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.79,0:01:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What slashes across is Linie der Torheit{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.79,0:02:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Soaring across the azure skies{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.37,0:02:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flügel der Freiheit{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.41,0:02:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,"Special Operations Squad"\N"Eve of the Counterattack, Part 2"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.25,0:02:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Trost District"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.70,0:02:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Old Scout Regiment Headquarters"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.37,0:02:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The old Scout Regiment headquarters...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.62,0:02:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you'd expect\Nfrom a renovated old castle,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.62,0:02:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks fancy and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.25,0:02:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But being so far\Nfrom the wall and the river
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.50,0:02:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it wound up being\Ntotally useless for the Scouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.45,0:02:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That was back in the early days,\Nwhen everyone had high hopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.08,0:03:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, to think that\Nthis oversized decoration
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,would end up as the\Nperfect holding place for you now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.16,0:03:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't get cocky, rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.08,0:03:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Come again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno if you're a Titan or what,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.70,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but don't assume Captain Levi's gonna stick\Nwith some wet-behind-the-ears brat like--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking on a horse is a guaranteed\Nway to bite your tongue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.58,0:03:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,First impressions are important.\NI had that rookie scared stiff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I think he was\Nshocked at how dumb you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.62,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the case,\Nit went exactly as I planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. You didn't used\Nto talk like that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.91,0:03:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If, by some chance,\Nyou're trying to imitate Captain Levi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.45,0:03:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...could you cut it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're nothing\Nlike him at all, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.83,0:03:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to nag me, Petra?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.54,0:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wanna act like you're my wife,\Nthere's more you need to do first...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you {\i1}had {\i0}bitten\Nyour tongue off and died,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.00,0:04:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,bragging all about how\Nmany Titans you've killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.95,0:04:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.75,0:04:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I bragged about you too,\Nwhile I was at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.95,0:04:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the members of the\NScout Regiment's Special Operations Squad...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.37,0:04:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Also known as the "Levi Squad."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.25,0:04:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheesh, you're disgraceful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.54,0:04:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Petra Rall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.87,0:04:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,10 Titans killed, and 48 kill-assists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.29,0:04:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oruo Bozad. 39 kills and 9 assists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.54,0:04:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They're as elite as they come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.08,0:04:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Eld Gin. 14 kills, 32 assists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.25,0:04:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunther Schultz. 7 kills, 40 assists.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.29,0:04:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Each is an accomplished Scout\Npersonally handpicked by Captain Levi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.00,0:04:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.16,0:05:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the people who'll end up\Nkilling me if I ever go out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.79,0:05:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There are weeds everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The place has really gone to hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.79,0:05:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It hasn't been used in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.29,0:05:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet it's plenty dusty on the inside too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a serious problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get to work at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.37,0:05:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've finished cleaning upstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.41,0:05:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where in this facility am I to sleep, Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Your room's in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.12,0:05:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The basement... again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.41,0:05:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.08,0:05:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have full control of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.62,0:05:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you turn\Ninto a Titan in your sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.45,0:05:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,we can keep you restrained right\Nthere in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That was one of the conditions I was\Ngiven when I took custody of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rule we have to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.33,0:06:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go check your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You take over here, Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.20,0:06:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You look disappointed, Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.29,0:06:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I hope you don't mind if\NI call you "Eren" like Captain Levi does.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.95,0:06:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He sets the rules here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.45,0:06:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.45,0:06:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, but did I really\Nlook disappointed just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not an unusual reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.62,0:06:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not quite the great, perfect hero\Nsociety makes him out to be, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.87,0:06:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}real {\i0}Captain Levi\Nis shorter than you'd expect,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,temperamental,\Ncrude, and unsociable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.04,0:06:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what surprises\Nme is how serious he is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.04,0:06:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,about adhering to the\Nhigher-ups' arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.45,0:06:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You thought that because\Nhe's strong and skilled
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.45,0:06:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn't have to follow\Nthe rules like everyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.12,0:06:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that he didn't\Ntake orders from anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.41,0:06:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really know the details myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think he might've\Nbeen like that at one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.04,0:07:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They say before he joined the Scouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.04,0:07:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Levi was an infamous rogue\Nin the capital's underground market.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.37,0:07:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.91,0:07:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.33,0:07:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.66,0:07:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but I hear he wound up\Nbeing dragged into the Scouts
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,after giving in to Commander Erwin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.75,0:07:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.79,0:07:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.95,0:07:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.04,0:07:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's completely unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.50,0:07:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.12,0:07:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,An expedition thirty days from now
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.50,0:07:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to establish a logistic base\Noutside the wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...and {\i0}newly-graduated rookies\Nwill be participating too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Assuming any rookies {\i1}do {\i0}join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.37,0:07:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the case, this all seems\Na bit too hasty if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.16,0:07:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren's current treatment is only temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.70,0:07:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to demonstrate to the\Ncentral powers as quickly as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that his existence is\Nbeneficial for humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.33,0:08:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, the Military Police\Nor someone else will interfere again--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.95,0:08:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you using rhetoric on me too, Erwin?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see your nose is\Nas sharp as ever, Miche.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as sharp as yours, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.83,0:08:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll fill you in when the time is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.58,0:08:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume our orders to remain on\Nstandby will last for a few more days,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.54,0:08:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I hear they're planning a\Nmajor expedition beyond the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}thirty {\i0}days from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that fresh graduates are going\Nto participate right off the bat too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true, Eld?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That seems pretty sudden to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,especially since the rookies already\Nhad to endure this latest Titan attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.87,0:08:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet those brats\Nwere scared out of their wits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.12,0:08:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this true, Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not in charge of\Ncoming up with missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.33,0:09:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But, knowing Erwin,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.29,0:09:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he's put far more thought\Ninto this than we have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.41,0:09:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, there's never\Nbeen a situation like this before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So many lives were lost establishing\Na route to reclaim Wall Maria.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when it seemed\Nlike it went up in smoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.50,0:09:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly a completely\Ndifferent hope has presented itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.33,0:09:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}still {\i0}hard to believe,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.00,0:09:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but how does this "changing into\Na Titan" thing work anyway, Eren?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.79,0:09:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories of it aren't very clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.58,0:09:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's like being in a trance...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.91,0:09:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I set it off by inflicting self-harm, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I take my hand like so and...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.29,0:09:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.29,0:09:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it,\Nwhy is this the only thing I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.91,0:09:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys know you can't\Nget any more info out of him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:09:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,than what's in the reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that {\i1}she {\i0}won't try, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.29,0:10:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Better hope {\i1}you {\i0}don't end up\Ndead when she tinkers with you, Eren.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Who's "she"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.95,0:10:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening,\Nmembers of the Levi Squad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.87,0:10:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How is castle life treating you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.33,0:10:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're early.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.66,0:10:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't help myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.20,0:10:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Section Commander Hange...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.95,0:10:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the wait, Eren!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm actually in charge of examining\Ntwo Titans we caught in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.41,0:10:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to help with\Nmy experiments tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so I came to get your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.00,0:10:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiments?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.62,0:10:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,--What would I have to do?\N--Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.37,0:10:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,...{\i1}the {\i0}most exhilarating thing of all, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.70,0:10:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Umm, I'm not in a position\Nto give permission myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.41,0:10:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have authority over\Nmyself, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.54,0:11:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Levi! What are Eren's\Nplans for tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Cleaning the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.66,0:11:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! It's decided!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.25,0:11:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Eren! I look forward to tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.66,0:11:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.25,0:11:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But what kind of Titan experiments\Nare we talking about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.33,0:11:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.54,0:11:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Err, as I said, what\Nkind of experiments are we...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop! Don't ask that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.45,0:11:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I {\i1}thought {\i0}you might\Nbe curious enough to ask...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.00,0:11:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know that badly, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.33,0:11:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you insist,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.79,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,then I guess I'd\Nbetter tell you allll about
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the little ones we recently caught...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.95,0:12:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I began by repeating\Nthe same experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've conducted\Nduring five previous captures.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,First was an attempt at communication.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.79,0:12:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you in pain?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.37,0:12:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Section Commander! You're too close!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice weather, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.75,0:12:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.66,0:12:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's dangerous,\NSection Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.62,0:12:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I had to conclude
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.70,0:12:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that there's no hope of\Ncommunicating with these ones either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.12,0:12:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,However, my time spent\Ninteracting with the Titans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.16,0:12:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,was fulfilling enough to make\Nme forget my daily exhaustion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.70,0:13:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Once upon a time, there existed\Na clan that ate humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.08,0:13:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't mean you Titans.\NI'm talking about a clan of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.83,0:13:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They would hide in\Ncaves on mountainsides
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.75,0:13:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and attack any\Ntravelers who passed by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They would steal their valuables,\Nkill them, and eat their flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we go again.\N{\i1}Another {\i0}of her naming ceremonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.12,0:13:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. What'd she\Ncall the last ones again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.83,0:13:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Chikatiloni and Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.12,0:13:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ultimately, they kept this\Nup for twenty-five years,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,during which time they supposedly\Npreyed upon over 500 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.87,0:13:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably more humans\Nthan {\i1}you've {\i0}eaten, in fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.75,0:13:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They also tried eating them\Nin all sorts of ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Making steaks out of rump meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.83,0:13:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Dicing up leg meat and adding it to a stew...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.08,0:13:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Grinding tough meat into patties and frying it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Making sausages from\Nblood clots and innards...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.79,0:14:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, they possessed\Nthe concept of "cooking"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.91,0:14:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where they differ from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.25,0:14:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this clan of cannibals\Nwas caught and executed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,after making one single mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.83,0:14:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you're just like them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.41,0:14:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys made the\Nmistake of attacking humankind
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.08,0:14:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and wound up caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm going to name you two
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.87,0:14:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,after the man who\Nwas the leader of this clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're "Sawney."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.20,0:14:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're "Beane."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.16,0:14:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to execute you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you, Sawney.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.75,0:14:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And you too, Beane.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.45,0:14:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all be friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.95,0:14:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how I named the\N7-meter Titan "Beane"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.79,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the 4-meter Titan "Sawney."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, I tested blocking them from sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.95,0:15:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,From the fact that Titans become\Nless active as the night progresses,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.25,0:15:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this experiment corroborates that\Nthey somehow use sunlight for energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.25,0:15:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from this that I found a\Nsubstantial difference between the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.37,0:15:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm. You did great, Sawney.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.00,0:15:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night. I'll see you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,While Sawney became sluggish\Nonly one hour out of sunlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.87,0:15:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure love to stay up late,\Ndon't you, Beane?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay. I'll hang out\Nwith you as long as you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.79,0:15:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...Beane was still his\Nenergetic self three hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It came as another shock to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.41,0:15:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't require food or water,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.91,0:15:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and even though they have vocal organs,\Nthey don't need to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.62,0:15:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing they need is sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.66,0:16:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm curious to know what happens\Nafter prolonged sunlight withdrawal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.37,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but I can't risk having them die, y'know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We've accidentally killed\Nprevious ones we've caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.91,0:16:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We tried decapitating some as an experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.62,0:16:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but accidentally cut the\Nnapes of their necks too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.54,0:16:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Their names were Chikatiloni and Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.83,0:16:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They had such cute smiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.66,0:16:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I did something truly terrible to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.08,0:16:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I never want that to happen again...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.08,0:16:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Hange...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.45,0:16:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After that...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.58,0:16:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The next step was\Nphysical contact with the Titans!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.87,0:16:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I tested to see if they felt pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.37,0:16:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Section Commander!\NThere's no need for {\i1}you {\i0}to scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.87,0:16:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do this and {\i1}not {\i0}scream!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.25,0:16:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Beane is in so much pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.75,0:17:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Beane! Hang in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.29,0:17:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to determine if\NTitans have any weaknesses
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.25,0:17:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,besides their napes, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.58,0:17:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an agonizing task.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.91,0:17:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawney...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.54,0:17:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey... I've stabbed you in the heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it not hurt?\NHow does it feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.41,0:17:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Compared to Beane,\NSawney seemed more introverted
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.33,0:17:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and didn't respond much at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.62,0:17:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.58,0:17:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.75,0:17:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Section Commander! Please step back!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.62,0:17:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost got me that time, Sawney!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.58,0:17:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're seriously gonna die!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So Sawney's not very\Ngood at expressing himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He just keeps trying to chomp my head off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.87,0:17:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Ms. Hange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.29,0:18:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so lighthearted\Nwhen dealing with Titans?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.41,0:18:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.79,0:18:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They're our natural enemy; they've driven\Nhumanity to the verge of extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.95,0:18:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you experienced the threat\Nthey pose countless times yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.70,0:18:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.08,0:18:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I've watched Titans kill friend\Nafter friend right before my very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first joined the Scouts,\NI fought the Titans out of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But, one day, I made a realization
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.04,0:18:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,after I kicked the severed\Nhead of a 3-meter-tall Titan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.58,0:18:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It was light. Unusually light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.70,0:18:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Titan's body, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.83,0:18:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.37,0:18:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When you think about it,\Nit shouldn't even be possible
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.79,0:18:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for such large creatures\Nto stand and walk on two legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.83,0:18:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Titan was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.00,0:19:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Severed limbs weren't nearly\Nas heavy as they should have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.08,0:19:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you transformed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm told your Titan body\Nappeared out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.12,0:19:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my belief
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that how they appear to us is\Nnothing like what they really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.20,0:19:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,For decades we've tried an offensive\Napproach that feeds off of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.87,0:19:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to try to view the Titans
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.87,0:19:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,from a different\Nangle than the existing one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.62,0:19:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It might end as a waste of time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.75,0:19:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...but I'm going to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.41,0:19:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Joining the Scouts has been\Nnothing but surprise after surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.91,0:19:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just Ms. Hange.\N{\i1}Everyone {\i0}is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.08,0:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's practically a haven of oddballs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.58,0:20:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.45,0:20:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A group of people that seeks change...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's {\i0}what the Scouts are all about!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.70,0:20:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Hange!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.79,0:20:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind telling me\Neven more about your experiments?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.25,0:20:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Are you sure?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.87,0:20:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.00,0:20:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be good\Nto know as much as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.70,0:20:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,before tomorrow's experiments!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.91,0:20:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.12,0:20:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm. I did gloss over\Na lot of things just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I should go into further detail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,--This could take a while...\N--That's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.12,0:20:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll start off with the hypothesis\NI had the first time we caught a Titan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As such, that experiment\Nprovided no new information!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.50,0:20:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they teach everyone\Nthis stuff during cadet training.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.50,0:20:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew all this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... I already knew it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.66,0:21:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}now {\i0}I'll explain things further
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,by going over everything\Nagain with my own theories!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.79,0:21:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.91,0:21:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.91,0:21:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,First is how Titans--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.04,0:21:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Section Commander Hange here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The test subjects...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.04,0:21:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of the Titans have been killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.33,0:21:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawney! Beane!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.29,0:21:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No... Tell me this isn't happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.95,0:21:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They were such valuable test subjects...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.29,0:21:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Did soldiers do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. They haven't yet\Nfound who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.04,0:21:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently both were killed\Nat the same time just before dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.83,0:21:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time the guards noticed,\Nwhoever did it had used ODM to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.12,0:21:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So a team of at least\Ntwo people planned this, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.75,0:21:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawney!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.25,0:21:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.70,0:21:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Section Commander Hange is raving mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.20,0:21:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How did this happen...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.66,0:22:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. The rest\Nis the Military Police's job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, Sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.70,0:22:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do {\i1}you {\i0}see here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.25,0:22:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think the enemy is?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.75,0:22:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.66,0:22:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. That was a strange thing to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.41,0:22:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If, by chance, I'm not me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.66,0:23:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}then who's to say that you're you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.91,0:23:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can you pick up the pieces of your heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.20,0:23:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that fell apart like a broken sand castle?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.33,0:23:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The voice of someone calling out{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.33,0:23:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}changed into ringing in my ears{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.41,0:23:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's as if time has stopped{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.58,0:23:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now wake up{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.37,0:23:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I made my way out of the deep darkness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.66,0:23:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I fled like a swift wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.91,0:23:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We used to be like living corpses,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.41,0:23:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but now we head beyond the walls{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.45,0:23:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Let's meet again{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.50,0:23:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in a place not on any map{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.54,0:24:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As the hunt for Sawney and\NBeane's killers gets underway,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.20,0:24:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mikasa, Armin, and the members\Nof the 104th Cadet Corps Class,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.54,0:24:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,with hopes and dreams of their own,\Nmust decide which regiment to join.
